The 2020 FIFA awards will be held in Zurich, Switzerland on Thursday 17 December. The awards will be stream-live on FIFA’s official website from 19:00 CET. The final three-man shortlists for Best FIFA Men’s Best Player Award are: Cristiano Ronaldo (Juventus and Portugal), Lionel Messi, (Barcelona and Argentina) and Robert Lewandowski (Bayern Munich and Poland). The final three-man shortlists for Best FIFA Men’s Goalkeeper Award are: Alisson (Brazil/ Liverpool), Manuel Neuer (Germany / Bayern München) and Jan Oblak (Slovenia / Atlético Madrid) The final three-man shortlists for this year’s Puskas Award include: Giorgian De Arrascaeta (URU) – Ceará SC v. CR Flamengo [Brasileirão – Brazil] (25 August 2019), Son Heung-min (KOR) – Tottenham Hotspur FC v. Burnley FC [Premier League – England] (7 December 2019) and Luis Suárez (URU) – FC Barcelona v. RCD Mallorca [LaLiga] – Spain] (7 December 2019). The final three-man shortlists for Best FIFA Women’s Coach are Emma Hayes (England / Chelsea FC Women), Jean-Luc Vasseur (France / Olympique Lyonnais) and Sarina Wiegman (Netherlands / Dutch national team).